<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-06-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-06-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="329" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3294/29.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">McCormick</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-06-11"><hi rend="italic">June 11,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Root informs Mr. McCormick that the consul at Marseilles telegraphed
                            that the imprisonment of Mr. Jacobs still continues, although the
                            extradition was authorized March 30. Mr. Root instructs Mr. McCormick to
                            ascertain if the continued detention is in accordance with the French
                            law.)</p>
                    </div>
